parameters: \n< Serena >Hmm...
\n< Serena >...Is that the Ogre...

Avoid a head-on fight, huh. I see, it
does have an intimidating presence to
say the least.\n< Serena >

\n< Serena >If we leave it be, such monsters will
swarm the city in droves.

\n< Serena >Then, we have no choice but to
exterminate them here!

\n< Serena >Phew... that was quite tough, but it
looks like it's taken care of.

\n< Serena >Just a few of them and they were this
strong. I don't even want to think about
what it would be like if there was a
swarm.

\n< Serena >Anyway, it's resolved. Let's head back
to report.

\n< Guild Master >Back already, lass? Looks like you
handled it well.

\n< Serena >Indeed, two orcs. I definitely took them
down.
\n< Guild Master >Oh, then the ears...
\n< Serena >...
\n< Guild Master >What? Don't tell me you...

\n< Serena >Well, since I did defeat them, there
shouldn't be a problem.

\n< Guild Master >Hey hey, we can't confirm the facts
without proof.

\n< Serena >Then send someone to check. I don't need
the reward this time, so use that to
cover the expenses.

\n< Guild Master >...Well, there's no other choice, so
we'll handle it that way this time.
Listen here, lass, when you take on a
job, you do it by the book.

\n< Guild Master >Exception handling, no matter how you
try to cover it up, will always put a
burden somewhere.

\n< Guild Master >Once you've accepted a job, you're a
professional, lass. Complete the request
as agreed and make sure to collect your
reward properly.
\n< Serena >I see. You have a point.
\n< Serena >But I still dislike certain things.

\n< Guild Master >Tsk... deducting the trouble fee from
the reward... This is all the reward for
this time.

\V[2501]\n< Serena > left. Alright,  with this one more case
is settled.
'　オークとやら、確かに屈強ではあったが我が音拳の前には'
'　何ほどの事もなかった。さぁ宿に戻ろう。'

E-Erika-sama...\n< Serena >

There there, are you alright? You're
safe now, Serena.\n< Erika >
You did well. Leave the rest to me!\n< Erika >
Drasshea!\n< Erika >
Alright, come here.\n< Erika >
?\n< Serena >
Come on, over here.\n< Erika >
What is it?\n< Serena >

No, I was just wondering if you wanted
to hug...\n< Erika >
I'm fine.\n< Serena >

You can cry and wail in my arms if you
want. I'll comfort you with some pats
and kind words.\n< Erika >
I'm fine... but I am grateful.\n< Serena >

Honestly, I had prepared myself for
death. And yet, I couldn't afford to die
in a place like this.\n< Serena >

Thank you, Erika-sama. You saved me...
truly.\n< Serena >
Ehehe.\n< Erika >

Well, I've been in a tight spot myself
before. Every time, someone has come to
my rescue just like this.\n< Erika >

If you're grateful for today, then
someday, if a fellow adventurer finds
themselves in a similar situation, help
them out.\n< Erika >
Understood. I will definitely do so.\n< Serena >
Alright then. Shall we head back?\n< Erika >

source. Is that alright?\n< Serena >

Something like venom was sprayed on
me... it's a white, sticky liquid.\n< Serena >
Huh?\n< Erika >

Ah, ah, ah.\n< Erika >
?\n< Serena >

Here you go, good work. This is your
reward.\n< Guild Master >

...No, haven't you heard the report?
Erika-sama assisted me this time. I was
merely helped. Please give this reward
to Erika-sama.\n< Serena >

To the guild, it doesn't really matter
either way. The request was completed
either way. So the reward will be given.
How you split the reward is up to you
folks to decide.\n< Guild Master >
Hmm, that is...\n< Serena >

Subcontracting and sub-subcontracting in
requests isn't exactly uncommon. If you
think about it, the adventurers' guild
system itself is like a giant
subcontractor.\n< Guild Master >

So as long as the result matches the
request, the guild doesn't care about
the process.\n< Guild Master >

Though I'll tell you, Erika will
probably refuse her share of the reward.\n< Guild Master >

Ah-. But let me tell you, that's not
really a good attitude for an
adventurer. Settling things with money
is ultimately the smoothest solution.\n< Guild Master >

But well... maybe treat her to a drink
at the tavern. That's what she enjoys
the most.\n< Guild Master >
...Understood.\n< Serena >
Thank you, Master-sama.\n< Serena >
You're welcome.\n< Guild Master >
\V[2501]\n< Serena >...That settles the matter then.
